WEBVTT

00:00:00.820 --> 00:00:10.680
Alif Lam Meem, Allah, La ilaha illa Huwa Al-Hibb Al-Qayyum,

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:18.180
Nazala alayka Al-Kitab Bil-Haqq Musabdiqa Lima Bayna Yadihi Wa Anzala Al-Tawrat Wa Al-Injeel,

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:22.260
Min Qabnu Hudan Li Al-Nas Wa Anzala Al-Furqan,

00:00:22.260 --> 00:00:27.540
Inna Allatheena Kaffaru Bi Ayat Allahi Lahum Adabuhu Shadeed,

00:00:27.540 --> 00:00:31.420
Wa Allahu Azizun Muthu Muthiqan,

00:00:31.620 --> 00:00:36.620
Inna Allaha La Yahta Aalayhi Shajjin Fi Al-Ardi Wa La Fi Al-Sama

00:00:36.620 --> 00:00:40.800
Assalamu Alaikum Wa Rahmatullahi Wa Barakatuh

00:00:40.800 --> 00:00:45.300
Bismillahir Rahmanir Raheem, Alhamdulillahi Wahdahu Wa Sallallahu wa Sallam

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:49.800
Wa Baraka Ala Malla Nabiyya Ba'dahu Wa Ala Aalihi Wa Ashaabihi Ajmaeen

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:53.300
We commence by praising Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:00:53.300 --> 00:00:57.300
sending blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:05.500
upon all the messengers that Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala has sent from the beginning of time up to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:10.700
We ask Allah to bless all of them and to bless their companions and those who supported them,

00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:18.100
those who struggled and strived to protect the deen that Allah had revealed and to pass it on to others in a way that today,

00:01:18.100 --> 00:01:19.800
Alhamdulillah, it has come to us.

00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:26.300
May Allah bless us all and grant us every form of goodness and make us from those who can continue the message

00:01:26.300 --> 00:01:29.300
and pass it through to our children and inshallah,

00:01:29.300 --> 00:01:33.200
may we be from amongst those whom the Almighty is pleased with.

00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:35.100
Beloved brothers and sisters,

00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:40.900
we had commenced yesterday the story of the ascension and the story of the journey by night,

00:01:40.900 --> 00:01:44.100
known as Al-Isra wal-Mi'raj.

00:01:44.100 --> 00:01:48.300
And this had happened as a gift to Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:01:48.300 --> 00:01:53.400
after what was known as the year of sorrow or grief or sadness,

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:58.100
where the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam had lost his uncle,

00:01:58.100 --> 00:02:01.100
he lost his wife Khadija radiallahu anha,

00:02:01.100 --> 00:02:08.600
he lost, meaning he went to Al-Ta'if and there also he was beaten and he was made to bleed

00:02:08.600 --> 00:02:10.100
and they did not accept the message,

00:02:10.100 --> 00:02:14.800
he came back to Makkah al-Mukarramah and persecutions continued there.

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:18.700
So Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam gave him a gift.

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:21.600
And in the eleventh year of prophethood,

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:26.700
Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam sent Jibreel alayhi wa sallam

00:02:26.700 --> 00:02:31.000
whilst the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was resting in the house of Ummu Hani

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:36.700
as we mentioned yesterday his cousin and that is where he was sleeping

00:02:36.700 --> 00:02:44.200
and Jibreel alayhi wa sallam came and took him to Al-Bayt al-Haram to where the Ka'ba is

00:02:44.200 --> 00:02:49.300
and Jibreel alayhi wa sallatu wa sallam there had,

00:02:49.300 --> 00:02:51.600
according to the narrations,

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:54.400
slit the chest of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:56.700
removed his heart and washed it with Zamzam,

00:02:56.700 --> 00:02:59.300
this was again, this had happened in the past

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:04.300
and it repeated itself according to the books of the Seerah thrice.

00:03:04.300 --> 00:03:06.700
May Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us the understanding,

00:03:06.700 --> 00:03:08.300
it was washed with Zamzam,

00:03:08.300 --> 00:03:12.800
the angels had come and washed the heart of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:03:12.900 --> 00:03:15.200
filled it with Yaqeen and as we know,

00:03:15.200 --> 00:03:21.100
the conviction is one of the most important things when it comes to belief in Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:24.000
and when it comes to Islam and Muslimin.

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
So the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was then taken on what was known as a buraq,

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.400
buraq an animal which is between a mule and a donkey,

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:37.800
a white animal and it took Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:03:37.800 --> 00:03:46.300
from Makkah al-Mukarramah all the way to Jerusalem in Bayt al-Maqdis in Jerusalem,

00:03:46.300 --> 00:03:49.500
Masjid al-Aqsa as we know it today

00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:52.900
and the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was there in no time

00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:57.700
but as he was traveling, he noticed everything on the way,

00:03:57.700 --> 00:04:01.000
subhanallah, he noticed everything on the way,

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:02.800
when he got there,

00:04:02.900 --> 00:04:09.100
subhanallah, he was made to meet some of the Prophets of Allah sallallahu wa ta'ala from amongst them,

00:04:09.100 --> 00:04:12.600
Jesus may peace be upon him, from amongst them,

00:04:12.600 --> 00:04:14.500
Moses may peace be upon him,

00:04:14.500 --> 00:04:16.800
Ibrahim, Abraham may peace be upon him,

00:04:16.800 --> 00:04:19.600
Isa, Musa, Ibrahim alayhi wa sallam,

00:04:19.600 --> 00:04:21.400
these were some of the Prophets who were there,

00:04:21.400 --> 00:04:26.000
Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam had instructed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:30.200
in Bayt al-Maqdis, in Masjid al-Aqsa in the particular place

00:04:30.200 --> 00:04:34.300
to lead them in prayer with two rak'ah of prayer

00:04:34.300 --> 00:04:37.400
and the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was an imam,

00:04:37.400 --> 00:04:42.400
he led them in prayer and then he came out and he was taken up to the heavens.

00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:46.000
We believe that before Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:49.300
Jesus may peace be upon him was taken up,

00:04:49.300 --> 00:04:52.100
he was taken up in body and soul

00:04:52.100 --> 00:04:55.400
and he was taken up alive before he was crucified,

00:04:55.400 --> 00:04:56.400
before he was killed,

00:04:57.300 --> 00:04:58.800
that there was no crucifixion,

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:00.400
nor was there any killing,

00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:02.000
but before they could harm him,

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.700
he was taken up to the heavens

00:05:04.700 --> 00:05:07.400
and at the moment he is there

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:10.600
and at the same time we also believe

00:05:10.600 --> 00:05:13.500
that he will be returning before the end of time,

00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:15.500
this is the belief of the Muslims,

00:05:15.500 --> 00:05:18.100
that Jesus may peace be upon him is alive,

00:05:18.100 --> 00:05:22.300
he has been taken up into the heavens by Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:05:22.300 --> 00:05:24.000
and he is there,

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:26.800
may Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam grant us a deep understanding,

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:29.000
he is in the second heaven

00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:32.300
and he will return to the earth closer to the end of time,

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:34.000
so it had happened in the past,

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.800
it is nothing impossible for Allah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:38.400
here it happened again,

00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:43.000
this time Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam was taken up to the heavens with Jibreel,

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:45.300
the angel Gabriel may peace be upon him,

00:05:45.300 --> 00:05:48.800
taken all the way up as they got to the first heaven,

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:50.900
a call, a call asking a question

00:05:50.900 --> 00:05:52.300
as they wanted to enter,

00:05:52.400 --> 00:05:53.900
who are you, I am Jibreel,

00:05:53.900 --> 00:05:57.400
who is with you, Muhammad is with me sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:05:57.400 --> 00:05:59.000
has he been sent for,

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.500
which means he is invited here,

00:06:00.500 --> 00:06:01.300
yes he is,

00:06:01.300 --> 00:06:02.900
it opened and he went in,

00:06:02.900 --> 00:06:07.500
lo and behold he met Adam alayhi sallatu wa sallam,

00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:08.800
first heaven,

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:12.100
so Adam alayhi sallam the first of human beings

00:06:12.100 --> 00:06:14.500
and the first of those who were sent to his own children

00:06:14.500 --> 00:06:16.900
in order to remind them what was right and wrong,

00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:19.400
he welcomed Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:20.800
not only as a child,

00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:22.800
because obviously he is the father,

00:06:22.800 --> 00:06:24.900
but also as a colleague,

00:06:24.900 --> 00:06:27.600
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us all

00:06:27.600 --> 00:06:30.900
and Alhamdulillah there after meeting him

00:06:30.900 --> 00:06:32.400
and being welcomed,

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:35.300
he proceeded up with Jibreel alayhi sallatu wa sallam

00:06:35.300 --> 00:06:36.800
to the second heaven,

00:06:36.800 --> 00:06:39.200
as they got up again the same question asked

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.000
and they were allowed in again

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:42.800
and he met two people,

00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:43.600
who were they,

00:06:43.600 --> 00:06:45.500
two prophets of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:06:45.500 --> 00:06:47.700
one was Jesus may peace be upon him

00:06:47.700 --> 00:06:49.200
and as we said,

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:52.700
Jesus Isa alayhi sallatu wa sallam is alive

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:55.900
and he was taken up in the condition

00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:57.900
that he was alive,

00:06:57.900 --> 00:07:02.200
so we believe that he did not die,

00:07:02.200 --> 00:07:04.100
may Allah's peace be upon him

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:08.000
and with him was Yahya alayhi sallatu wa sallam

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:09.400
the one known as John,

00:07:09.400 --> 00:07:12.000
John the Baptist may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.100
bless them both and grant them goodness

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:16.600
and may we be from amongst those who learn a lesson

00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:18.500
from the beautiful life of Jesus

00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:19.800
may peace be upon him

00:07:19.800 --> 00:07:22.100
and from his sacrifices and miracles

00:07:22.100 --> 00:07:25.100
and the same time may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:07:25.100 --> 00:07:26.800
make us from those who realize

00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:28.800
that the end of prophethood came

00:07:28.800 --> 00:07:30.400
with Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:33.000
we are fortunate to be from his ummah,

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.400
after that he proceeded to the next heaven

00:07:35.400 --> 00:07:37.300
when he proceeded in fact he was welcomed

00:07:37.300 --> 00:07:39.200
by the two and the same thing happened

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:41.500
where they welcomed him,

00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:42.800
congratulated him

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:44.900
and he proceeded to the third heaven,

00:07:44.900 --> 00:07:46.500
in the third heaven,

00:07:46.500 --> 00:07:49.500
he met Yusuf alayhi sallatu wa sallam

00:07:49.500 --> 00:07:52.000
the most handsome of all the messengers

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:53.800
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:07:53.800 --> 00:07:57.200
the hadith says he was granted half of all beauty

00:07:57.200 --> 00:07:58.100
subhanallah

00:07:58.100 --> 00:08:00.300
so the other half, the other 50%

00:08:00.300 --> 00:08:02.000
is split between the rest of us

00:08:02.000 --> 00:08:03.800
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:08:03.800 --> 00:08:05.000
grant us goodness

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:06.600
and make us from amongst those really

00:08:06.600 --> 00:08:09.000
who can appreciate whatever we look like

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.300
I've actually said it in the past

00:08:10.300 --> 00:08:12.700
your identity you did not apply for it

00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:14.100
it's Allah who chose it for you

00:08:14.100 --> 00:08:15.100
don't get upset

00:08:15.100 --> 00:08:16.400
the person this way that way

00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.700
every one of us has something

00:08:18.700 --> 00:08:20.300
that will not be perfect

00:08:20.300 --> 00:08:21.300
you know you have one shoulder

00:08:21.300 --> 00:08:22.400
a little bit low a little bit

00:08:22.400 --> 00:08:23.500
no one notices it

00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:25.000
you have a nose slightly this way

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:26.300
one eye a bit bigger smaller

00:08:26.300 --> 00:08:27.800
one brow this way that way

00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:30.200
don't worry you cannot get it perfect

00:08:30.200 --> 00:08:30.700
number one

00:08:30.700 --> 00:08:31.700
number two is

00:08:31.700 --> 00:08:32.900
if you become conscious

00:08:32.900 --> 00:08:34.700
you only become from amongst those

00:08:34.700 --> 00:08:36.100
who are ungrateful to Allah

00:08:36.100 --> 00:08:37.000
don't worry

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:38.600
whatever you look like is unique

00:08:38.600 --> 00:08:40.400
that is you that what makes you you

00:08:40.400 --> 00:08:42.500
Allahu akbar

00:08:42.500 --> 00:08:43.500
may Allah be pleased with us

00:08:43.500 --> 00:08:45.000
and may we be pleased also

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:47.000
with Allah's decisions for us

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:49.100
so he was welcomed again

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:51.000
MashaAllah Yusuf a.s.w.

00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:51.900
welcomed him

00:08:51.900 --> 00:08:53.500
and thereafter they proceeded

00:08:53.500 --> 00:08:55.000
to the next heaven

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:56.200
another messenger of Allah

00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:57.200
subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:08:57.200 --> 00:08:59.000
Idris a.s.w.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:00.900
he was there

00:09:00.900 --> 00:09:02.700
he met Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:09:02.700 --> 00:09:04.200
and Jibreel he welcomed them

00:09:04.200 --> 00:09:05.000
and so on

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:07.200
as they progressed up the heavens

00:09:07.200 --> 00:09:08.500
every time they were asked

00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:09.300
who was it

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:10.500
the answer came Jibreel

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:11.200
who is with you

00:09:11.200 --> 00:09:12.600
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.000
has he been called for

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:14.900
yes he has

00:09:14.900 --> 00:09:16.100
then the gates open

00:09:16.100 --> 00:09:17.900
and they go up into the next heaven

00:09:17.900 --> 00:09:18.800
the next heaven

00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:21.400
they met Harun a.s.w.

00:09:21.400 --> 00:09:23.200
that was the fifth heaven

00:09:23.200 --> 00:09:25.000
Harun a.s.w.

00:09:25.000 --> 00:09:25.800
he welcomed them

00:09:25.800 --> 00:09:26.400
and MashaAllah

00:09:26.400 --> 00:09:27.900
thereafter they proceeded

00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:29.300
to one of the messengers

00:09:29.300 --> 00:09:30.600
of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:32.000
who went through a lot

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:34.900
Musa a.s.w.

00:09:34.900 --> 00:09:36.500
and the Prophet Musa a.s.w.

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:37.400
welcomed them

00:09:37.400 --> 00:09:38.100
and MashaAllah

00:09:38.100 --> 00:09:39.800
he was so happy to meet them

00:09:39.800 --> 00:09:40.400
and thereafter

00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:41.700
as they are progressing

00:09:41.700 --> 00:09:42.900
one narration says

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:44.400
he began to cry

00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:45.300
Musa a.s.w.

00:09:45.300 --> 00:09:46.600
one narration says this

00:09:46.600 --> 00:09:48.500
it's important that we make mention of it

00:09:48.500 --> 00:09:49.500
and when he was asked

00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:50.000
what is it

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:50.700
he says

00:09:50.700 --> 00:09:52.700
because you are a messenger

00:09:52.700 --> 00:09:54.900
who will have many more followers

00:09:54.900 --> 00:09:56.700
on the day of Qiyamah than myself

00:09:56.700 --> 00:09:58.200
subhanallah

00:09:58.200 --> 00:09:59.300
and then they proceeded

00:09:59.300 --> 00:10:00.700
to the next heaven

00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:03.300
where they met Ibrahim a.s.w.

00:10:03.300 --> 00:10:04.100
seventh heaven

00:10:04.100 --> 00:10:05.400
the Prophet Abraham

00:10:05.400 --> 00:10:07.300
upon the highest level

00:10:07.300 --> 00:10:09.200
the father of most of the prophets

00:10:09.200 --> 00:10:10.400
the father of the prophets

00:10:10.400 --> 00:10:11.400
who came after him

00:10:11.400 --> 00:10:13.700
including Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:10:13.700 --> 00:10:14.400
when they met him

00:10:14.400 --> 00:10:16.000
MashaAllah he welcomed them

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:17.500
and they saw what is known as

00:10:17.500 --> 00:10:19.300
Al-Bait ul-Ma'mur

00:10:19.300 --> 00:10:20.300
it is a house

00:10:20.300 --> 00:10:22.000
that is visited by the angels

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:24.800
reportedly 70,000 angels

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:26.400
enter this place of worship

00:10:26.400 --> 00:10:28.000
which is above the Kaaba

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:29.700
directly above the Kaaba

00:10:29.700 --> 00:10:30.700
going very high

00:10:30.700 --> 00:10:32.600
above the seventh heaven

00:10:32.600 --> 00:10:34.700
and the angels engage in the

00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:36.500
Ibadah of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:36.500 --> 00:10:37.500
every day

00:10:37.500 --> 00:10:40.000
70,000 angels enter

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:43.000
and the same angels do not return

00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:45.300
the next day there is another 70,000

00:10:45.300 --> 00:10:47.300
and that happens every single day

00:10:47.300 --> 00:10:48.300
up to the end of time

00:10:48.300 --> 00:10:49.400
Allahu Akbar

00:10:49.400 --> 00:10:51.700
so imagine the number of angels they are

00:10:51.700 --> 00:10:53.100
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:54.900
bless us and grant us goodness

00:10:54.900 --> 00:10:56.000
do you know

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:57.500
that the Quran makes mention

00:10:57.500 --> 00:10:59.900
of the dua of the angels

00:10:59.900 --> 00:11:02.600
the angels ask Allah

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:04.700
to forgive those who believe

00:11:04.700 --> 00:11:06.300
and the angels ask Allah

00:11:06.300 --> 00:11:08.900
to forgive those who are repenting

00:11:08.900 --> 00:11:12.400
and the angels engage in seeking forgiveness

00:11:12.400 --> 00:11:14.300
for those on earth

00:11:14.300 --> 00:11:20.500
والملائكة يسبحون بحمد ربهم

00:11:20.500 --> 00:11:25.700
ويستغفرون لمن في الأرض

00:11:25.700 --> 00:11:28.600
the angels declare the praise of their Rabb

00:11:28.600 --> 00:11:29.900
and they seek forgiveness

00:11:29.900 --> 00:11:31.500
for those on earth

00:11:31.500 --> 00:11:33.500
subhanallah look at how lucky we are

00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:35.200
when we are sitting now here

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:38.300
anyone who is engaged in anything wherein

00:11:38.300 --> 00:11:40.100
they are becoming closer to Allah

00:11:40.100 --> 00:11:41.300
subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:43.200
the angels have encircled them

00:11:43.200 --> 00:11:44.600
and the blessings of Allah

00:11:44.600 --> 00:11:45.700
descending upon them

00:11:45.700 --> 00:11:47.200
and the angels are praying for them

00:11:47.200 --> 00:11:48.100
making dua for them

00:11:48.100 --> 00:11:49.400
seeking forgiveness for them

00:11:49.400 --> 00:11:51.600
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:11:51.600 --> 00:11:53.000
and may He make us feel that

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:54.400
this is why we say

00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:56.300
don't miss an occasion

00:11:56.300 --> 00:11:58.300
to learn more of your religion

00:11:58.300 --> 00:12:00.000
to purify your knowledge

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:01.600
and to authenticate it

00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:03.400
and to learn as much as you can

00:12:03.400 --> 00:12:05.100
in order for you to get closer

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:07.000
to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:08.400
as the days pass

00:12:08.400 --> 00:12:10.100
instead of getting further away

00:12:10.100 --> 00:12:12.300
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala take us close

00:12:13.300 --> 00:12:16.100
now a quick mention before we go further

00:12:16.900 --> 00:12:18.700
the journey by night

00:12:18.700 --> 00:12:20.900
from Mecca to Jerusalem

00:12:20.900 --> 00:12:22.300
was known as Al-Israa

00:12:22.300 --> 00:12:25.800
this an entire surah has been named after

00:12:25.800 --> 00:12:33.800
subhana alladhi asraa bi abdihi layla min al masjid al haram

00:12:33.800 --> 00:12:37.100
ila al masjid al aqsa

00:12:37.100 --> 00:12:40.300
alladhi barakna hawlah

00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:44.000
linuriya hu min ayaatina

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:50.300
inna huwa assami'ul basid

00:12:50.300 --> 00:12:52.600
glory be to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:54.800
who took his slave on a journey by night

00:12:54.800 --> 00:12:57.400
from Mecca to Jerusalem

00:12:57.400 --> 00:13:00.900
the place around which Allah has blessed

00:13:00.900 --> 00:13:02.400
in order for him

00:13:02.400 --> 00:13:04.800
meaning Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:13:04.800 --> 00:13:07.500
to be shown by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:07.500 --> 00:13:10.400
some of the signs of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:10.400 --> 00:13:13.000
so this is a sign of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:14.600
people cannot deny it

00:13:14.600 --> 00:13:16.000
especially today

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:20.200
because we know how quick we can make a journey

00:13:20.200 --> 00:13:22.000
to the other corner of the world

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:23.800
and we know that technology

00:13:23.800 --> 00:13:26.400
has progressed even further

00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:30.000
than what a passenger aircraft can take you

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:32.500
meaning as quick as a passenger aircraft

00:13:32.500 --> 00:13:34.600
the passenger aircrafts are very slow

00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:36.000
they had had a concord

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:37.200
why did they stop it?

00:13:37.200 --> 00:13:38.800
because of a few disasters

00:13:38.800 --> 00:13:42.400
but they have means of transport

00:13:42.400 --> 00:13:44.700
even faster than a concord

00:13:44.700 --> 00:13:48.100
it's just that people cannot risk

00:13:48.100 --> 00:13:49.100
making use of it

00:13:49.100 --> 00:13:50.200
Allahu Akbar

00:13:50.200 --> 00:13:52.000
if you take a look at the missiles they have

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:53.000
within a few seconds

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:54.400
they arrive where they have to

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:55.600
Allah protect us

00:13:55.600 --> 00:13:56.600
Subhanallah

00:13:56.600 --> 00:13:58.600
imagine if someone had to sit on one of them

00:13:58.600 --> 00:13:59.800
Allahu Akbar

00:13:59.800 --> 00:14:02.000
make sure there's no warhead there insha'Allah

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:04.000
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.200
and grant us goodness

00:14:05.200 --> 00:14:06.800
and may he make us from amongst those

00:14:06.800 --> 00:14:08.100
who realize and understand

00:14:08.100 --> 00:14:09.400
nothing is impossible for Allah

00:14:09.400 --> 00:14:11.300
also going up to the heavens

00:14:11.300 --> 00:14:13.600
we made mention of Isa alayhi salam

00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:15.000
already having done that

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:16.700
and he remained there

00:14:16.700 --> 00:14:18.800
the difference is Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:14:18.800 --> 00:14:20.500
came back to tell us

00:14:20.500 --> 00:14:21.800
he actually came back

00:14:21.800 --> 00:14:23.600
and he informed us so accurately

00:14:23.600 --> 00:14:25.300
as we will see in a few moments

00:14:25.300 --> 00:14:28.700
that ascension was known as mi'raj

00:14:28.700 --> 00:14:30.600
the mi'raj going up

00:14:30.600 --> 00:14:32.800
the buraq did not go up with them

00:14:32.800 --> 00:14:35.900
but it was Jibril alayhi salatu wa salam

00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:37.800
who took Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:14:37.800 --> 00:14:40.200
in what is known as mi'raj

00:14:40.200 --> 00:14:42.800
like an elevator going all the way up

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:43.700
by the will of Allah

00:14:43.700 --> 00:14:45.200
how exactly it happened

00:14:45.200 --> 00:14:46.700
that we will only find out

00:14:46.700 --> 00:14:48.800
when we ourselves get to the akhirah

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:49.600
but we believe

00:14:49.600 --> 00:14:51.600
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:14:51.600 --> 00:14:54.200
that firm belief and conviction

00:14:54.200 --> 00:14:56.400
so thereafter Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:14:56.400 --> 00:14:58.300
was made to go even higher

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:00.900
and he spoke with Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:02.700
he spoke with his rab

00:15:02.700 --> 00:15:04.100
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:04.100 --> 00:15:06.000
spoke to Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:08.200
on this occasion of mi'raj

00:15:08.200 --> 00:15:09.500
when he had gone up

00:15:09.500 --> 00:15:11.500
beyond the seventh heaven

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:13.900
there is something at the end of the seventh heaven

00:15:13.900 --> 00:15:16.700
a huge lote tree

00:15:16.700 --> 00:15:19.200
known as sidratul muntaha

00:15:19.200 --> 00:15:21.100
it is the final, the last tree

00:15:21.100 --> 00:15:23.300
a huge tree describing

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:24.600
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:26.400
describes its fruit and its leaves

00:15:26.400 --> 00:15:28.900
as being like the ears of elephants and so on

00:15:28.900 --> 00:15:31.900
and subhanallah a huge tree

00:15:31.900 --> 00:15:33.500
you cannot see its beginning

00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:34.700
and cannot see its end

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:35.900
a huge tree

00:15:35.900 --> 00:15:38.300
and that depicts the end of the seventh heaven

00:15:38.300 --> 00:15:40.100
beyond which is what I named

00:15:40.100 --> 00:15:42.200
baytul ma'mur moments ago

00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:43.500
we spoke about it

00:15:43.500 --> 00:15:46.200
the house that is visited by the angels

00:15:46.200 --> 00:15:48.200
and the house wherein

00:15:48.200 --> 00:15:50.200
the ibadah of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:52.200
takes place by the angels

00:15:52.200 --> 00:15:54.900
and Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:15:54.900 --> 00:15:56.500
met Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:56.500 --> 00:16:00.200
and the discussion that happened

00:16:00.200 --> 00:16:02.100
within that discussion

00:16:02.100 --> 00:16:04.900
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala gave

00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:07.000
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:09.600
a gift, a gift of what?

00:16:09.600 --> 00:16:11.500
a gift of salaat

00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:12.600
salaat, this prayer

00:16:12.600 --> 00:16:14.800
we pray it five times a day

00:16:14.800 --> 00:16:17.200
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala told him

00:16:17.200 --> 00:16:18.800
that your followers should pray

00:16:18.800 --> 00:16:21.000
fifty times a day

00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:22.100
that's a gift

00:16:22.100 --> 00:16:23.200
imagine salaat is a gift

00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:25.100
it protects us from so much

00:16:25.100 --> 00:16:26.500
it disciplines us

00:16:26.500 --> 00:16:27.400
it trains us

00:16:27.400 --> 00:16:28.500
control of your gaze

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:29.700
control of your movements

00:16:29.700 --> 00:16:30.900
control of what goes in

00:16:30.900 --> 00:16:31.900
and out of your mouth

00:16:31.900 --> 00:16:32.800
everything in salaat

00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:34.400
I cannot eat in salaat

00:16:34.400 --> 00:16:36.000
because I need to train myself

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:37.300
and at the same time

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:39.900
act of worship for Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:16:39.900 --> 00:16:42.400
we have so many medical benefits of salaat

00:16:42.400 --> 00:16:44.800
although the prime aim of reading salaat

00:16:44.800 --> 00:16:46.200
is for the pleasure of Allah

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:48.400
but we achieved so much

00:16:48.400 --> 00:16:51.600
you know they call it a by-product

00:16:51.600 --> 00:16:54.000
it might not be exactly what you had aimed for

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:55.400
but you're getting so much more

00:16:55.400 --> 00:16:57.000
they've thrown in freebies

00:16:57.000 --> 00:16:59.000
so to speak in our language today

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:00.700
you have perks, mashaAllah

00:17:00.700 --> 00:17:02.100
you know you have a job, mashaAllah

00:17:02.100 --> 00:17:03.300
you get a salary

00:17:03.300 --> 00:17:05.000
and at the same time you get perks

00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:06.200
so because I'm working here

00:17:06.200 --> 00:17:07.300
I get this and I get that

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:08.900
my children's school fees is paid

00:17:08.900 --> 00:17:09.800
and this happens

00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:11.600
even if I've got ten children

00:17:11.600 --> 00:17:12.700
everyone will benefit

00:17:12.700 --> 00:17:13.800
subhanallah

00:17:13.800 --> 00:17:15.300
this is a different example

00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:16.200
because it's Allah

00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:17.800
وَلِلَّهِ الْمَثَلُ الْأَعْلَى

00:17:17.800 --> 00:17:19.400
Allah has the highest of examples

00:17:19.400 --> 00:17:21.700
so the only point being raised is

00:17:21.700 --> 00:17:23.500
when we fulfill salaat

00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:25.900
we will have so many side benefits

00:17:25.900 --> 00:17:28.200
although the main purpose of fulfilling

00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:29.800
it would be for the pleasure of Allah

00:17:29.800 --> 00:17:32.000
in order to obey the instruction of Allah

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:33.000
wholeheartedly

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:33.900
so it was a gift

00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:35.300
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:17:35.300 --> 00:17:37.300
was coming down now

00:17:37.300 --> 00:17:38.400
and when he came down

00:17:38.400 --> 00:17:39.500
Musa alayhi wassallam

00:17:39.500 --> 00:17:40.900
was quick to ask him

00:17:40.900 --> 00:17:42.100
what happened there

00:17:42.100 --> 00:17:43.900
so he says well this is what happened

00:17:43.900 --> 00:17:45.700
and I spoke to Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:17:45.700 --> 00:17:47.800
and I was given a gift of 50 salah

00:17:47.800 --> 00:17:49.500
he says no go back

00:17:49.500 --> 00:17:51.100
go back to do what

00:17:51.100 --> 00:17:53.900
go back and ask for a decrease

00:17:53.900 --> 00:17:56.200
because your ummah is not going to manage

00:17:56.200 --> 00:17:57.500
50 salah a day

00:17:57.500 --> 00:17:58.600
they're not going to manage

00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:00.000
so the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wassallam

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:01.300
went back up

00:18:01.300 --> 00:18:03.600
and it was revised downwards

00:18:03.600 --> 00:18:06.400
by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to 45

00:18:06.400 --> 00:18:07.600
as he's coming back

00:18:07.600 --> 00:18:09.200
Musa alayhi wassallam sends him back

00:18:09.200 --> 00:18:09.900
go back again

00:18:09.900 --> 00:18:11.400
45 still no good

00:18:11.400 --> 00:18:12.500
and in fives

00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:14.200
it kept on coming down

00:18:14.200 --> 00:18:16.300
until it stopped at five

00:18:16.300 --> 00:18:17.900
subhanallah five

00:18:17.900 --> 00:18:18.900
and on top of that

00:18:18.900 --> 00:18:20.000
Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wassallam

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:21.000
was told

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:24.300
that those who fulfill the five correctly

00:18:24.300 --> 00:18:25.600
will have a reward

00:18:25.600 --> 00:18:27.700
multiplied by ten

00:18:27.700 --> 00:18:29.200
so equivalent to 50

00:18:29.200 --> 00:18:30.300
subhanallah

00:18:30.300 --> 00:18:31.800
we still

00:18:31.800 --> 00:18:32.300
imagine I

00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:33.500
whenever I read this hadith

00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:34.700
I think of one thing

00:18:34.700 --> 00:18:36.500
I think what if it was me or you there

00:18:36.500 --> 00:18:37.300
even the five

00:18:37.300 --> 00:18:38.300
we would have probably said

00:18:38.300 --> 00:18:39.100
you know what

00:18:39.100 --> 00:18:40.300
let's revise it downwards

00:18:40.300 --> 00:18:42.100
to perhaps have it one a day

00:18:42.100 --> 00:18:44.200
you know or maybe even five a year

00:18:44.200 --> 00:18:45.600
or something of that nature

00:18:45.600 --> 00:18:46.500
Allah forgive us

00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:47.200
wallahi

00:18:47.200 --> 00:18:48.500
why I say this is

00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:49.900
perhaps that might not be the case

00:18:49.900 --> 00:18:50.700
but

00:18:50.700 --> 00:18:51.800
we are so lazy

00:18:51.800 --> 00:18:53.900
even the five that we do fulfill

00:18:53.900 --> 00:18:55.200
if we fulfill them

00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:56.800
with such laziness

00:18:56.800 --> 00:18:58.800
what if we had had 50

00:18:58.800 --> 00:18:59.700
subhanallah

00:18:59.700 --> 00:19:00.700
don't we owe

00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:02.000
Musa alayhi wassallam

00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:03.300
subhanallah

00:19:03.300 --> 00:19:05.600
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them all

00:19:05.600 --> 00:19:08.200
these were the prophets all related to one another

00:19:08.200 --> 00:19:09.100
masha'allah

00:19:09.100 --> 00:19:10.500
and they really

00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:13.000
they served us in a very great way

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:15.500
salawatu rabbi wa salamuhu alayhim jami'an

00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:17.100
may Allah's peace and blessings

00:19:17.100 --> 00:19:18.600
be upon them all

00:19:18.600 --> 00:19:19.800
amin

00:19:19.800 --> 00:19:20.500
so masha'allah

00:19:20.500 --> 00:19:22.700
this was the gift of salah

00:19:22.700 --> 00:19:24.500
and the hadith continues to say

00:19:24.500 --> 00:19:26.200
whoever fulfills a deed

00:19:26.200 --> 00:19:27.700
multiplied by 10

00:19:27.700 --> 00:19:28.800
and on top of that

00:19:28.800 --> 00:19:29.900
on the same occasion

00:19:29.900 --> 00:19:31.500
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wassallam

00:19:31.500 --> 00:19:33.100
was told

00:19:33.100 --> 00:19:35.600
something that brings tears to the eyes

00:19:35.600 --> 00:19:37.900
whoever fulfills a good deed

00:19:37.900 --> 00:19:42.200
that good deed shall be multiplied by 10

00:19:42.200 --> 00:19:44.900
and whoever intends to do a good deed

00:19:44.900 --> 00:19:48.100
but did not manage to fulfill the intention

00:19:48.100 --> 00:19:50.500
they will have a reward for that

00:19:50.500 --> 00:19:53.800
and whoever intends to do a bad deed

00:19:53.800 --> 00:19:55.900
but does not do it

00:19:55.900 --> 00:19:57.700
neither will they have a reward

00:19:57.700 --> 00:19:58.800
nor a sin

00:19:58.800 --> 00:20:00.900
so you plan to do a bad deed

00:20:00.900 --> 00:20:02.500
but you didn't do it

00:20:02.500 --> 00:20:04.500
no reward, no sin

00:20:04.500 --> 00:20:06.800
and whoever plans to do a bad deed

00:20:06.800 --> 00:20:08.300
and executes it

00:20:08.300 --> 00:20:10.800
will get one sin next to their name

00:20:10.800 --> 00:20:11.900
Allahu Akbar

00:20:11.900 --> 00:20:13.600
look at how the evil

00:20:13.600 --> 00:20:15.900
is not multiplied by the mercy of Allah

00:20:15.900 --> 00:20:17.500
but the good is multiplied

00:20:17.500 --> 00:20:18.600
by the mercy of Allah

00:20:18.600 --> 00:20:20.000
subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:20.000 --> 00:20:21.500
this is what we were granted

00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:23.800
at that point of

00:20:23.800 --> 00:20:25.000
mi'raj

00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:26.300
when Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:26.300 --> 00:20:28.400
spoke to Muhammad salallahu alayhi wassallam

00:20:28.400 --> 00:20:29.600
there is a question

00:20:29.600 --> 00:20:30.800
did

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:33.100
Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wassallam

00:20:33.100 --> 00:20:35.700
see Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:35.700 --> 00:20:37.700
he was asked that when he returned

00:20:37.700 --> 00:20:38.900
did you see Allah

00:20:38.900 --> 00:20:39.700
he says

00:20:39.700 --> 00:20:41.700
nurun anna araha

00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:43.200
Aisha radiallahu anha

00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:44.500
was also asked

00:20:44.500 --> 00:20:46.500
did Rasulullah salallahu alayhi wassallam

00:20:46.500 --> 00:20:47.700
see Allah

00:20:47.700 --> 00:20:48.900
speaking we know

00:20:48.900 --> 00:20:50.200
but did he see Allah

00:20:50.200 --> 00:20:51.500
subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:52.200
she said

00:20:52.200 --> 00:20:54.400
nurun anna araha

00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:56.000
he is such nur

00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:58.900
how would it have been possible for him to see him

00:20:58.900 --> 00:21:00.800
which means he did not see him

00:21:00.800 --> 00:21:02.600
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:04.300
grant us the sight

00:21:04.300 --> 00:21:06.800
that seeing of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:06.800 --> 00:21:07.900
is a gift

00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:09.800
which is kept for

00:21:09.800 --> 00:21:10.600
jannah

00:21:10.600 --> 00:21:11.600
for paradise

00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:13.200
those who enter paradise

00:21:13.200 --> 00:21:15.800
they will all have

00:21:15.800 --> 00:21:18.000
whatever they want in paradise

00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:19.000
and on top of that

00:21:19.000 --> 00:21:20.600
they will be asked

00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:22.600
do you have whatever you want

00:21:22.600 --> 00:21:24.400
and they will all say

00:21:24.400 --> 00:21:25.400
let me word it differently

00:21:25.400 --> 00:21:26.600
and we will all say

00:21:26.600 --> 00:21:28.600
Alhamdulillah may Allah make us from them

00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:29.600
and we will all say

00:21:29.600 --> 00:21:30.300
yes

00:21:30.300 --> 00:21:32.700
and then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala will say

00:21:32.700 --> 00:21:35.000
I have something more for you

00:21:40.000 --> 00:21:41.200
for those who have done good

00:21:41.200 --> 00:21:42.900
they will get good in return

00:21:42.900 --> 00:21:44.400
and we will give them even more

00:21:44.400 --> 00:21:45.600
they have excess

00:21:45.600 --> 00:21:47.200
what is more

00:21:47.200 --> 00:21:50.300
so Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala will remove the barrier

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:52.000
between them and him

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:54.500
and they will see him for the first time

00:21:54.500 --> 00:21:57.000
and that will be the biggest gift

00:21:57.000 --> 00:21:59.300
the biggest gift ever

00:21:59.300 --> 00:22:02.600
given to any of the creatures of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:02.600 --> 00:22:05.200
may Allah make us from amongst them

00:22:05.200 --> 00:22:06.700
imagine to look at your Rabb

00:22:06.700 --> 00:22:07.900
today we look at people

00:22:07.900 --> 00:22:09.500
and we say mashaAllah good looking

00:22:09.500 --> 00:22:11.200
and we look at motor vehicles

00:22:11.200 --> 00:22:13.400
and we look at cars and houses

00:22:13.400 --> 00:22:14.900
and so many different things

00:22:14.900 --> 00:22:16.200
and we look at sceneries

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:17.400
and we get excited

00:22:17.400 --> 00:22:19.500
what about the maker of all that

00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:20.900
subhanAllah

00:22:20.900 --> 00:22:22.500
Rabbul Izzati wal Jalal

00:22:22.500 --> 00:22:23.900
may Allah grant us

00:22:23.900 --> 00:22:25.400
the sweetness of looking at him

00:22:25.400 --> 00:22:28.700
as is in the dua of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:22:28.700 --> 00:22:30.300
so when he came down

00:22:30.300 --> 00:22:32.200
sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:22:32.300 --> 00:22:33.800
and the same evening

00:22:33.800 --> 00:22:35.500
he was back in his same bedding

00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:37.400
the bedding still warm

00:22:37.400 --> 00:22:38.900
which means

00:22:38.900 --> 00:22:40.900
it had not yet struck dawn

00:22:40.900 --> 00:22:41.800
and he was back

00:22:41.800 --> 00:22:43.200
subhanAllah

00:22:43.200 --> 00:22:44.600
and he tells

00:22:44.600 --> 00:22:45.600
those who are around him

00:22:45.600 --> 00:22:47.700
Ummuhani according to one of the narrations

00:22:47.700 --> 00:22:48.400
what had happened

00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:50.100
and immediately

00:22:50.100 --> 00:22:51.200
they believe

00:22:51.200 --> 00:22:52.800
immediately because they knew

00:22:52.800 --> 00:22:55.900
that this is the messenger of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:22:55.900 --> 00:22:57.100
and

00:22:57.100 --> 00:22:58.600
he said I am going to go out

00:22:58.600 --> 00:23:00.100
and announce this to Quraysh

00:23:00.600 --> 00:23:02.200
according to one narration says

00:23:02.200 --> 00:23:03.300
don't go out and announce it

00:23:03.300 --> 00:23:04.700
because they might not believe you

00:23:04.700 --> 00:23:06.000
they'll make a mockery of you

00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:07.300
he says no

00:23:07.300 --> 00:23:09.400
he has been told to deliver the message

00:23:09.400 --> 00:23:10.700
so he went out

00:23:10.700 --> 00:23:11.700
and he announced it

00:23:11.700 --> 00:23:13.000
he called the people

00:23:13.000 --> 00:23:15.600
and the Abu Jahal and them came running

00:23:15.600 --> 00:23:16.900
because they wanted to know

00:23:16.900 --> 00:23:18.800
what is this man calling us for now

00:23:18.800 --> 00:23:20.800
when we've been persecuting him so much

00:23:20.800 --> 00:23:21.800
now what does he want

00:23:21.800 --> 00:23:23.400
maybe he wants to strike a deal

00:23:23.400 --> 00:23:24.300
they went forth

00:23:24.300 --> 00:23:25.500
and he says

00:23:25.500 --> 00:23:28.400
I have been taken up at night

00:23:28.400 --> 00:23:29.500
into the seven heavens

00:23:29.500 --> 00:23:31.400
and I traveled from here to Jerusalem

00:23:31.400 --> 00:23:32.200
all in one night

00:23:32.200 --> 00:23:33.800
and I returned and came back

00:23:33.800 --> 00:23:36.000
before the morning

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:37.100
they started laughing

00:23:37.100 --> 00:23:38.300
scoffing

00:23:38.300 --> 00:23:39.800
what a joke

00:23:39.800 --> 00:23:42.000
this is impossible

00:23:42.000 --> 00:23:44.200
and then they spoke to Abu Bakr

00:23:44.200 --> 00:23:45.800
Al-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:23:45.800 --> 00:23:47.500
asked him a question

00:23:47.500 --> 00:23:49.000
would you believe if someone tells you

00:23:49.000 --> 00:23:50.800
that they went from here to Baytul Maqdis

00:23:50.800 --> 00:23:52.100
in one night and from there

00:23:52.100 --> 00:23:54.600
same night going all the way up to the seven heavens

00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:56.000
coming down and so on

00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:57.500
your friend says this

00:23:57.500 --> 00:23:59.100
he says well if he says it

00:23:59.100 --> 00:24:00.200
I believe it

00:24:00.200 --> 00:24:01.200
if he says it

00:24:01.200 --> 00:24:02.700
I believe it

00:24:02.700 --> 00:24:04.500
he was the first one

00:24:04.500 --> 00:24:08.700
whom without even a pause

00:24:08.700 --> 00:24:10.600
immediately said

00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:11.400
if he said it

00:24:11.400 --> 00:24:12.300
it's the truth

00:24:12.300 --> 00:24:15.300
this is why he was known as Al-Siddiq

00:24:15.300 --> 00:24:18.700
the one who was not only truthful himself

00:24:18.700 --> 00:24:21.500
but the one who recognized the truth

00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:23.800
immediately and surrendered to it

00:24:23.800 --> 00:24:25.000
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:24:25.000 --> 00:24:26.100
make us from those

00:24:26.100 --> 00:24:27.500
who recognize the truth

00:24:27.500 --> 00:24:29.600
and who can surrender to it immediately

00:24:29.600 --> 00:24:30.500
as I said yesterday

00:24:30.500 --> 00:24:32.000
sometimes we know the truth

00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:33.200
but we don't surrender to it

00:24:33.200 --> 00:24:34.200
because of our weakness

00:24:34.200 --> 00:24:35.500
why is that the case

00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:37.500
may Allah strengthen us to dress properly

00:24:37.500 --> 00:24:40.400
may He strengthen us to fulfill our prayers properly

00:24:40.400 --> 00:24:42.200
wallahi don't be mistaken

00:24:42.200 --> 00:24:43.900
there are people across the globe

00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:46.200
who are far less fortunate than us

00:24:46.200 --> 00:24:48.100
who are making an effort

00:24:48.100 --> 00:24:50.000
to obey Allah's instructions

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:52.400
and their effort is far more fruitful than ours

00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:53.800
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:24:53.800 --> 00:24:55.700
bless us and make it easy for us

00:24:55.700 --> 00:24:58.700
so the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:24:58.700 --> 00:25:00.900
thereafter was asked questions

00:25:00.900 --> 00:25:02.000
by the people of Quraysh

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:03.200
because there was a buzz

00:25:03.200 --> 00:25:05.000
now in Quraysh people are talking

00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:06.600
did you hear this madman

00:25:06.600 --> 00:25:07.400
what happened to him

00:25:07.400 --> 00:25:08.100
he came here

00:25:08.100 --> 00:25:10.000
he says he did this and did that

00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:11.300
and these people who believe him

00:25:11.300 --> 00:25:13.700
are even more mad

00:25:13.700 --> 00:25:15.100
there were some believers

00:25:15.100 --> 00:25:16.200
who were weak

00:25:16.200 --> 00:25:17.700
who had taken a little bit of time

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:19.800
before they actually surrendered to it

00:25:19.800 --> 00:25:21.100
but subhanallah

00:25:21.100 --> 00:25:22.300
the kuffar of Quraysh

00:25:22.300 --> 00:25:24.700
the disbelievers came up with questions

00:25:24.700 --> 00:25:27.800
some of them had visited Jerusalem

00:25:27.800 --> 00:25:30.300
so what had happened is

00:25:30.300 --> 00:25:32.100
they asked a question

00:25:32.100 --> 00:25:33.600
describe for us Jerusalem

00:25:33.600 --> 00:25:34.500
describe it

00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:36.400
so Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:25:36.400 --> 00:25:37.600
started describing

00:25:37.600 --> 00:25:39.700
very accurately

00:25:39.700 --> 00:25:40.700
door by door

00:25:40.700 --> 00:25:41.800
house by house

00:25:41.800 --> 00:25:42.900
describing everything

00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:43.600
this is the

00:25:43.600 --> 00:25:44.500
this is how you enter

00:25:44.500 --> 00:25:45.200
this is what happens

00:25:45.200 --> 00:25:45.700
this is where

00:25:45.700 --> 00:25:46.400
this is this is where

00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:47.100
that is

00:25:47.100 --> 00:25:48.800
they were shocked and gobsmacked

00:25:48.800 --> 00:25:50.100
no response

00:25:50.100 --> 00:25:51.000
the people of Quraysh

00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:52.300
no response

00:25:52.300 --> 00:25:53.900
so they asked him another question

00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:54.900
they said okay

00:25:54.900 --> 00:25:56.100
our caravan

00:25:56.100 --> 00:25:57.400
that is on its way

00:25:57.400 --> 00:25:58.400
did you see it

00:25:58.400 --> 00:25:59.700
he said yes I saw it

00:25:59.700 --> 00:26:00.900
and you know what

00:26:00.900 --> 00:26:01.900
it is at the moment

00:26:01.900 --> 00:26:03.100
in such and such a place

00:26:03.100 --> 00:26:04.700
returning to Medina

00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:06.000
and there is a white camel

00:26:06.000 --> 00:26:07.700
which has a black spot on it

00:26:07.700 --> 00:26:09.000
that is right in the front

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:10.200
and if you expect it

00:26:10.200 --> 00:26:11.400
on such and such a day

00:26:11.400 --> 00:26:12.500
it will be coming

00:26:12.500 --> 00:26:13.300
sorry in Makkah

00:26:13.300 --> 00:26:14.300
sorry not Medina

00:26:14.300 --> 00:26:15.600
it will be arriving

00:26:15.600 --> 00:26:17.000
at this particular place

00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:18.100
and it will be coming here

00:26:18.100 --> 00:26:18.900
and you will see it

00:26:18.900 --> 00:26:20.000
and lo and behold

00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:21.700
exactly what happened

00:26:21.700 --> 00:26:23.000
exactly what happened

00:26:23.000 --> 00:26:24.300
and he mentioned the water

00:26:24.300 --> 00:26:26.100
and he mentioned how much was on it

00:26:26.100 --> 00:26:26.700
and what happened

00:26:26.700 --> 00:26:28.200
and how many camels they were

00:26:28.200 --> 00:26:28.900
and the people

00:26:28.900 --> 00:26:30.200
and all the details

00:26:30.200 --> 00:26:30.700
Subhanallah

00:26:30.700 --> 00:26:31.700
so much so

00:26:31.700 --> 00:26:33.300
that when for a moment

00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:34.200
he had paused

00:26:34.200 --> 00:26:36.900
because he was trying to remember

00:26:36.900 --> 00:26:39.000
what exactly had happened

00:26:39.000 --> 00:26:41.200
Allah Subhanahu wa Ta'ala

00:26:41.200 --> 00:26:43.200
put the image again in front of him

00:26:43.200 --> 00:26:44.500
as he was sitting there

00:26:44.500 --> 00:26:45.900
and then he began to describe it

00:26:45.900 --> 00:26:47.400
and it's in front of him

00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:48.400
and he says

00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:49.900
not only this caravan

00:26:49.900 --> 00:26:51.200
you are asking about

00:26:51.200 --> 00:26:52.400
another two caravans

00:26:52.400 --> 00:26:53.500
he described them

00:26:53.500 --> 00:26:54.500
and where they were

00:26:54.500 --> 00:26:55.200
and what happened

00:26:55.200 --> 00:26:57.100
Subhanarabbiya al-A'la

00:26:57.100 --> 00:26:59.800
Quraysh still gobsmacked

00:26:59.800 --> 00:27:00.900
Allahu Akbar

00:27:00.900 --> 00:27:02.800
Quraysh still gobsmacked

00:27:02.800 --> 00:27:04.400
there is an important point

00:27:04.400 --> 00:27:05.900
at that juncture

00:27:05.900 --> 00:27:08.100
they said this man is a magician

00:27:08.100 --> 00:27:10.100
and he is a fortune teller

00:27:10.100 --> 00:27:11.000
he can tell fortune

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:12.100
that's what it is

00:27:12.100 --> 00:27:14.100
and they quickly just sidelined him

00:27:14.100 --> 00:27:16.400
whereas he came with Quran

00:27:16.400 --> 00:27:18.100
that prohibited

00:27:18.100 --> 00:27:19.800
not only fortune telling

00:27:19.800 --> 00:27:20.900
but magic as well

00:27:20.900 --> 00:27:22.500
this evening we heard verses

00:27:22.500 --> 00:27:23.300
SubhanAllah

00:27:23.300 --> 00:27:24.500
powerful verses

00:27:24.500 --> 00:27:27.300
Musa Alayhi Salatu wa Salam

00:27:27.300 --> 00:27:29.000
what did he say?

00:27:29.000 --> 00:27:33.300
قال موسى ما جئتن به السح

00:27:33.300 --> 00:27:35.400
Moses told the Pharaoh

00:27:35.400 --> 00:27:36.200
and the magicians

00:27:36.200 --> 00:27:38.100
that what you people have come with is magic

00:27:38.100 --> 00:27:39.000
what I have come with

00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:41.200
is a sign from Allah

00:27:41.200 --> 00:27:42.400
and then he says

00:27:42.400 --> 00:27:45.600
إن الله سيبطله

00:27:45.600 --> 00:27:50.800
إن الله لا يصلح عمل المفسدين

00:27:50.800 --> 00:27:53.200
Allah will destroy that magic

00:27:53.200 --> 00:27:55.800
magic is doomed completely

00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:57.600
it will be destroyed

00:27:57.600 --> 00:28:00.400
because Allah does not allow those

00:28:00.400 --> 00:28:03.100
who engage in corruption on the earth

00:28:03.100 --> 00:28:04.200
to succeed

00:28:04.200 --> 00:28:05.700
they won't succeed

00:28:05.700 --> 00:28:07.800
the deeds of those who are corrupt

00:28:07.800 --> 00:28:08.600
they don't succeed

00:28:08.600 --> 00:28:09.800
no matter what

00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:11.400
so these were verses we heard

00:28:11.400 --> 00:28:13.400
that same Quran

00:28:13.400 --> 00:28:15.200
how can the man who brought it

00:28:15.200 --> 00:28:16.700
engage in magic

00:28:16.700 --> 00:28:18.600
and how can the man who brought it

00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:19.400
who says

00:28:19.400 --> 00:28:21.300
من أتى عرافا أو كاهنا

00:28:21.300 --> 00:28:22.900
فصدقه بما أخبر

00:28:22.900 --> 00:28:25.000
فقد كفر بما أنزل على محمد

00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:26.600
صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:28:26.600 --> 00:28:28.600
whoever goes to a fortune teller

00:28:28.600 --> 00:28:29.800
or a soothsayer

00:28:29.800 --> 00:28:32.000
and believes what the fortune teller

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:33.100
has to say

00:28:33.100 --> 00:28:35.800
has disbelieved in what Muhammad came with

00:28:35.800 --> 00:28:36.800
SubhanAllah

00:28:36.800 --> 00:28:37.600
may Allah save goddess

00:28:37.600 --> 00:28:38.600
and the same man

00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:40.900
they're calling him a fortune teller

00:28:40.900 --> 00:28:41.800
do you see

00:28:41.800 --> 00:28:43.000
الله أكبر

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:44.400
Allah opens the doors

00:28:44.400 --> 00:28:45.700
for whomever he wishes

00:28:45.700 --> 00:28:47.000
and he closes the doors

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:48.700
upon whomever he wishes

00:28:48.700 --> 00:28:49.900
may Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:28:49.900 --> 00:28:50.900
open our doors

00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:52.300
what is important is

00:28:52.300 --> 00:28:54.000
when Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:28:54.000 --> 00:28:55.300
went up into the heavens

00:28:55.300 --> 00:28:57.100
he was taken on a tour

00:28:57.100 --> 00:28:58.800
he was taken on a tour

00:28:58.800 --> 00:29:00.700
a tour to see what

00:29:00.700 --> 00:29:01.800
to see heaven

00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:03.300
and to see hell

00:29:03.300 --> 00:29:05.400
and he saw certain things in heaven

00:29:05.400 --> 00:29:07.400
and he saw certain things in hell

00:29:07.400 --> 00:29:09.800
he saw in quite a bit of detail

00:29:09.800 --> 00:29:11.500
how the people of hell

00:29:11.500 --> 00:29:12.900
were being punished

00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:14.100
and when he came back

00:29:14.100 --> 00:29:15.300
he told us

00:29:15.300 --> 00:29:17.100
that the people who eat interest

00:29:17.100 --> 00:29:19.200
were being punished in a specific way

00:29:19.200 --> 00:29:20.800
those who commit adultery

00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:22.700
were being punished in a specific way

00:29:22.700 --> 00:29:24.200
those who engage in this sin

00:29:24.200 --> 00:29:26.600
were being punished in a specific way

00:29:26.600 --> 00:29:27.300
and then he says

00:29:27.300 --> 00:29:29.400
Ya Bilal, O Bilal

00:29:29.400 --> 00:29:30.400
what is it that you do?

00:29:30.400 --> 00:29:31.200
do

00:29:31.200 --> 00:29:32.700
when I was in

00:29:32.700 --> 00:29:33.800
touring paradise

00:29:33.800 --> 00:29:36.300
I heard your footsteps in paradise

00:29:36.300 --> 00:29:38.800
سمعت خشخشتك في الجنة

00:29:38.800 --> 00:29:40.600
he says I heard the خشخش

00:29:40.600 --> 00:29:42.400
خشخش is the sound of a little slipper

00:29:42.400 --> 00:29:44.600
when you're walking

00:29:44.600 --> 00:29:47.100
and later on it was discovered

00:29:47.100 --> 00:29:48.700
that Bilal ibn Rabah

00:29:48.700 --> 00:29:50.300
who was a slave

00:29:50.300 --> 00:29:52.600
who was freed by the Muslims

00:29:52.600 --> 00:29:55.200
he was a slave of Umayyah ibn Khalaf

00:29:55.200 --> 00:29:57.100
and he was freed by Abu Bakr al-Siddiq

00:29:57.100 --> 00:29:58.600
رضي الله عنه

00:29:58.600 --> 00:30:00.700
he was from Africa

00:30:00.700 --> 00:30:02.500
it was later discovered

00:30:02.500 --> 00:30:04.700
that whenever he made wudu

00:30:04.700 --> 00:30:06.100
whenever he washed

00:30:06.100 --> 00:30:08.700
he did not allow the wudu to expire

00:30:08.700 --> 00:30:11.000
without reading two rak'ah of salah

00:30:11.000 --> 00:30:12.600
soon as he completed his wudu

00:30:12.600 --> 00:30:14.700
