confirmed this also in a narration

00:48:36.880 --> 00:48:38.680
he was the second person

00:48:38.680 --> 00:48:39.780
who had accepted Islam

00:48:39.780 --> 00:48:42.180
but was unable to propagate the message

00:48:42.180 --> 00:48:44.780
so this was the first

00:48:44.780 --> 00:48:47.480
the beginnings of Islam in Medina Munawwara

00:48:47.480 --> 00:48:49.080
but it was not spread

00:48:49.080 --> 00:48:53.780
until Allah favored the people of Medina

00:48:53.780 --> 00:48:54.980
that day of Buath

00:48:54.980 --> 00:48:56.480
there was such a great war

00:48:56.480 --> 00:48:59.080
that most of the leaders were killed

00:48:59.080 --> 00:49:01.180
now when the leaders are gone what happens

00:49:01.180 --> 00:49:03.780
there is a bit of chaos

00:49:03.780 --> 00:49:05.080
when the leaders are there

00:49:05.080 --> 00:49:06.680
and Islam is presented to them

00:49:06.680 --> 00:49:09.280
what did they used to say in Makkah

00:49:09.280 --> 00:49:10.280
they used to say no ways

00:49:10.280 --> 00:49:11.480
we're going to lose our chair

00:49:11.480 --> 00:49:12.680
our seat

00:49:12.680 --> 00:49:13.280
you know

00:49:13.280 --> 00:49:14.580
when there's a man sitting on a chair

00:49:14.580 --> 00:49:16.480
he doesn't want anyone else to sit on that chair

00:49:16.480 --> 00:49:17.380
it happens

00:49:17.380 --> 00:49:19.080
so for as long as he's alive

00:49:19.080 --> 00:49:19.680
there's no hope

00:49:19.680 --> 00:49:20.680
the minute he's dead

00:49:20.680 --> 00:49:21.480
what will happen

00:49:21.480 --> 00:49:22.380
there is a lot of hope

00:49:22.380 --> 00:49:24.180
because now things can change

00:49:24.180 --> 00:49:25.280
Allahu Akbar

00:49:25.280 --> 00:49:27.480
so this is what happened in Medina Munawwara

00:49:27.480 --> 00:49:29.480
when those leaders were dead

00:49:29.480 --> 00:49:31.180
they were looking for someone to lead them

00:49:31.180 --> 00:49:33.280
they were divided into two main clans

00:49:33.280 --> 00:49:35.880
Al-Auth and Khazraj

00:49:35.880 --> 00:49:37.480
these two used to fight

00:49:37.480 --> 00:49:38.280
forever and ever

00:49:38.280 --> 00:49:39.980
they've always been fighting

00:49:39.980 --> 00:49:41.080
and they were at war

00:49:41.080 --> 00:49:43.080
they killed so many of one another

00:49:43.080 --> 00:49:44.680
now that there was a massive war

00:49:44.680 --> 00:49:46.980
where so many of their leaders had passed away

00:49:46.980 --> 00:49:48.580
there was a little bit of a stalemate

00:49:48.580 --> 00:49:49.880
and they were just licking their wounds

00:49:49.880 --> 00:49:51.280
and counting their losses

00:49:51.280 --> 00:49:53.180
and in the meantime the festival happened

00:49:53.180 --> 00:49:54.580
when that festival happened

00:49:54.580 --> 00:49:56.480
Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:49:56.480 --> 00:49:59.680
met a group of six of them

00:49:59.680 --> 00:50:01.480
we need to remember these six

00:50:01.480 --> 00:50:03.280
Subhanallah

00:50:03.280 --> 00:50:04.580
he told them where are you from

00:50:04.580 --> 00:50:05.580
they said we're from Yathrib

00:50:05.580 --> 00:50:07.780
can I sit and talk to you for a little while

00:50:07.780 --> 00:50:08.380
he said yes

00:50:08.380 --> 00:50:09.680
you know if we sit and read

00:50:09.680 --> 00:50:12.880
the etiquette of Rasulullah صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:50:12.880 --> 00:50:13.880
as a messenger

00:50:13.880 --> 00:50:15.680
how he sat with these people

00:50:15.680 --> 00:50:17.380
how he presented Islam

00:50:17.380 --> 00:50:18.680
how he respected them

00:50:18.680 --> 00:50:20.480
how he answered their questions

00:50:20.480 --> 00:50:22.680
we will learn a lot of diplomacy

00:50:22.680 --> 00:50:25.280
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us that

00:50:25.280 --> 00:50:28.280
how we speak to people is very important

00:50:28.280 --> 00:50:29.880
sometimes this tongue

00:50:29.880 --> 00:50:31.880
can destroy a home, a house

00:50:31.880 --> 00:50:33.680
because we don't know how to talk

00:50:33.780 --> 00:50:35.780
and what can happen Subhanallah

00:50:35.780 --> 00:50:38.580
because we've used our tongue correctly

00:50:38.580 --> 00:50:40.080
we can build relations

00:50:40.080 --> 00:50:42.280
even with people who may be enemies

00:50:42.280 --> 00:50:44.380
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us

00:50:44.380 --> 00:50:45.680
so he met six people

00:50:45.680 --> 00:50:48.580
and he sat down and had a chat with them

00:50:48.580 --> 00:50:50.480
he gave them the story of Islam

00:50:50.480 --> 00:50:51.680
these six were

00:50:51.680 --> 00:50:52.980
As'ad ibn Zurara

00:50:52.980 --> 00:50:53.980
may Allah be pleased with him

00:50:53.980 --> 00:50:55.180
later on to be known

00:50:55.180 --> 00:50:56.980
Awf ibn Harith

00:50:56.980 --> 00:50:58.180
Rafi ibn Malik

00:50:58.180 --> 00:50:59.380
Tutba ibn Amir

00:50:59.380 --> 00:51:00.480
Uqba ibn Amir

00:51:00.480 --> 00:51:01.880
and Jabir ibn Abdullah

00:51:01.880 --> 00:51:03.380
these were people from Khazraj

00:51:03.480 --> 00:51:04.880
when they were told

00:51:04.880 --> 00:51:07.080
in the 11th year of prophethood

00:51:07.080 --> 00:51:09.480
that this is the message of Allah

00:51:09.480 --> 00:51:11.480
and there is heaven and there is hell

00:51:11.480 --> 00:51:13.380
and you are answerable and so on

00:51:13.380 --> 00:51:15.080
they told each other do you know what

00:51:15.080 --> 00:51:17.680
this is what the Jews are speaking about all the time

00:51:17.680 --> 00:51:20.080
and now that the Jews have always been telling us

00:51:20.080 --> 00:51:21.580
there's a prophet about to come

00:51:21.580 --> 00:51:23.280
we've got a feeling this is the man

00:51:23.280 --> 00:51:24.680
and let us believe in him quickly

00:51:24.680 --> 00:51:26.080
because the message is exactly

00:51:26.080 --> 00:51:27.980
what they have been saying it would be

00:51:27.980 --> 00:51:29.080
and if we believe in him

00:51:29.080 --> 00:51:29.780
Subhanallah

00:51:29.780 --> 00:51:31.080
we will be successful

00:51:31.080 --> 00:51:33.280
the six of them accepted Islam

00:51:33.280 --> 00:51:35.180
and they went back to their people

00:51:35.180 --> 00:51:36.480
and started teaching Islam

00:51:36.480 --> 00:51:37.580
Insha'Allah tomorrow

00:51:37.580 --> 00:51:39.380
we will see how the migration

00:51:39.380 --> 00:51:42.180
to Medina Munawwara had started

00:51:42.180 --> 00:51:43.380
and how it occurred

00:51:43.380 --> 00:51:45.080
by the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:51:45.080 --> 00:51:46.380
may Allah bless us

00:51:46.380 --> 00:51:48.380
may he bless not only these six

00:51:48.380 --> 00:51:49.580
whom we have just mentioned

00:51:49.580 --> 00:51:50.980
but all those who struggled

00:51:50.980 --> 00:51:52.080
and strived for the deal

00:51:52.080 --> 00:51:53.680
and may he make us from amongst them

00:51:53.680 --> 00:51:56.080
wa salallahu wa sallam wa baraka ala nabina Muhammad

00:51:56.080 --> 00:51:57.180
subhanallahi bi hamdihi

00:51:57.180 --> 00:51:58.580
subhanaka allahum wa bi hamdiki

00:51:58.580 --> 00:52:00.280
nashhadu alla ilaha illa anta

00:52:00.280 --> 00:52:02.080
nastaghfiruka wa natubu ilayki

00:52:03.280 --> 00:52:08.380
alif la ammeen

00:52:08.380 --> 00:52:12.580
allahu la ilaha illa huwa alhiyyul tayyum
